Make a graph

Tell R: 1. That we’re using ggplot 2. What data we’re using, and what variables we want to plot 3. What type of graph we’re creating

ggplot(data = THIS, aes(x = THIS, y = THIS)) +
  geom_THIS()

Now let’s create a graph of CI visitation:

Line graph

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_line()

Scatterplot

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_point()

Column graph

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_col()

Area graph

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) +
  geom_area()

Intro to customizing ggplot graphs

  • color = (update point or line color)
  • fill = (update the fill characteristic of an element)
  • linetype =
  • pch = (value) = size =
  • alpha =

Only have aes() when we’re changing an element based on a variable

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) + 
  geom_line(color = "limegreen", 
            linetype = "dashed")

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) + 
  geom_point(color = "blue",
             pch = 17,
             size = 4, 
             alpha = 0.5)

ggplot(data = ci_np, aes(x = year, y = visitors)) + 
  geom_point(color = "blue",
             pch = 4,
             size = 4, 
             alpha = 0.9)
